  "prompt": "Up to what rank in GATE ECE can we expect a call from BARC for an interview?",
  "response": "The exact rank in GATE ECE (Electronics and Communication Engineering) required to receive a call for an interview from BARC (Bhabha Atomic Research Centre) can vary from year to year based on several factors, including the number of applicants, the total vacancies, and the specific requirements set by BARC for that recruitment cycle.\n\nHowever, historically, candidates with a GATE rank under 500 have often received interview calls from BARC for ECE positions. Some years, candidates with ranks up to 1000 have also been considered, especially if the overall pool of applicants is smaller.\n\nIt's essential to keep in mind that BARC also considers other factors such as the subject paper, the number of vacancies in specific disciplines, and the overall performance of candidates in the GATE exam. To have the most accurate information, refer to the official BARC recruitment notification for the specific year you are interested in or reach out to past candidates about their experiences.",
